snippet.title: Celebrating Mardi Gras in God's Light (Barron Trump Sings)
snippet.description:
Celebrating Mardi Gras in God's Light

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
Verse 1
In the heart of New Orleans, where the streets come alive,
Mardi Gras colors in a vibrant dive.
Purple for justice, gold for power's might,
Green for faith, shining ever bright.

Pre-Chorus
Masks and beads, laughter fills the air,
But beneath the revelry, a call to care.
As Lent approaches, we prepare our hearts,
Reflecting on grace, where renewal starts.

Chorus
Oh, Mardi Gras, a joyful song,
In God's embrace, where we belong.
We dance and sing, our spirits high,
Thankful for blessings from the sky.

Verse 2
Feasting today, for tomorrow we fast,
Cherishing moments, making them last.
A time to indulge, yet souls align,
With God's love, eternally divine.

Pre-Chorus
Carnival's end ushers in the Lent,
Forty days of reflection, time well spent.
From Fat Tuesday's cheer to Ash Wednesday's grace,
We seek God's presence in every place.

Chorus
Oh, Mardi Gras, a joyful song,
In God's embrace, where we belong.
We dance and sing, our spirits high,
Thankful for blessings from the sky.

Bridge
Through parades and music, we find our way,
Guided by faith, day by day.
Mardi Gras shines with a deeper glow,
A testament to the love we know.

Chorus
Oh, Mardi Gras, a joyful song,
In God's embrace, where we belong.
We dance and sing, our spirits high,
Thankful for blessings from the sky.

Outro
So as the beads glitter and the trumpets play,
We honor God in our festive display.
Mardi Gras, a time to rejoice and pray,
Embracing His love, today and always.
